commit.message:
Read the password from stdin if desired

Use the common convention: "-" means to use stdin

Signed-off-by: Steve McIntyre <steve.mcintyre@pexip.com>
Improved manual
Sort central directory entries in ascending order by offset
Simplify base64 decoding in script.c
Fixed memory corruption
Intercepted X509_V_FLAG_CHECK_SS_SIGNATURE verify error
Supported CRL decoding in DER and PEM format

Ignore missing PKCS#9 signing time field (NID_pkcs9_signingTime: 1.2.840.113549.1.9.5) in the CMS_ContentInfo structure.
Timestamping time for verification is get from embedded content in this CMS_ContentInfo structure.
Set the NONCE field in a TSA request
Initial 2.9-dev commit
Update workflow components

Release 2.8

Signed-off-by: Michał Trojnara <Michal.Trojnara@stunnel.org>
Fixed memory leaks
Changelog update
Simplify BIO chain free up and FILE_FORMAT_CTX cleanup
Simplify checking whether a signature exists
Fixed cross-signed root CA certificate
Fix handling of printf format specifiers

NEWS.md entry for Microsoft PowerShell signing

Closes #37
Install python@3.8 on macOS required for the Github Actions CI
Fix fuzzer error - corrupted data content
Disable curl dependence
Update Windows build documentation
Connect to CRL Distribution Points through the configured proxy when verifying

Fix python 3 compatibility in server_http.py (#350)

Building osslsigncode fails on systems with older versions of Python 3 due to the server_http.py script, part of the test procedure. This script requires the ThreadingHTTPServer module, introduced in Python version 3.7.

A workaround has been implemented to create a ThreadingHTTPServer locally, ensuring backward compatibility with older Python versions.

Fix python 3 compatibility in server_http.py (#350)

Building osslsigncode fails on systems with older versions of Python 3 due to the server_http.py script, part of the test procedure. This script requires the ThreadingHTTPServer module, introduced in Python version 3.7.

A workaround has been implemented to create a ThreadingHTTPServer locally, ensuring backward compatibility with older Python versions.
